{Misterton}is a village in the north of Nottinghamshire.It has a population of around four thousand.There are two main types of work{farming}and{ {engineering. }
The Chesterfield Canal runs through the village and is used by fishermen and pleasure craft. At{West Stockwith},a small village nearby,there is the canal basin for the junction between the River Trent and the Chesterfield Canal.
Although it is very close to the Lincolnshire border (6miles from {Gainsborough}),the area is administered by the Bassetlaw Council, which is part of Nottinghamshire County Council
